misconceptions.inferred_category_name: No conceptual error (correct right-rotation mental model)
misconceptions.student_thought_process: The student believes that to right-shift with wrap-around, you must save the last element, move each element one index to the right (from the end toward the start to avoid overwriting), then place the saved last element into index 0.
misconceptions.conceptual_gap: No gap: this matches Java’s array semantics and correct in-place rotation logic. Iterating from the end prevents overwriting values before they are copied.
misconceptions.error_manifestation: No error; produces correct shifted array output for N>0 and also behaves correctly for N==0 (prints just 'Shifted: ').
